te,March2 141\nWhile the followers of Christ have sinned, they have not given\nthemselves to the control of evil. They have put away their sins,\nand have sought the Lord in humility and contrition, and the divine\nAdvocate pleads in their behalf. He who has been most abused by\ntheir ingratitude, who knows their sin, and also their repentance,\ndeclares, “The Lord rebuke thee, O Satan. I gave My life for these\nsouls. They are graven upon the palms of My hands.”—The Review"
