asting hills, in the lofty trees, in the opening buds and the\ndelicate flowers. All speak to us of God. The Sabbath, ever pointing\nto Him who made them all, bids men and women open the great\nbook of nature and trace therein the wisdom, the power, and the love\nof the Creator.—Patriarchs and Prophets, 47, 48."
