les in regard to the\ntrue observance of the Sabbath, he would have discerned the nature\nand character of the work that Christ had performed.... The work\nthat Christ had done was in harmony with the sanctification of the\nSabbath day. The people on this side and that side wondered and\nweregladattheworkthathadbeenwroughtforthesufferingwoman;\nand there were those whose hearts were touched, whose minds were\nenlightened,whowouldhaveacknowledgedthemselvesthedisciples\nof Christ, had it not been for the lowering, angry countenances of"
