eginning, God looked upon all He had made, and pro-\nnounced it very good. The curse was brought upon the earth in\nconsequence of sin. But shall this curse be multiplied by increas-\ning sin? Ignorance is doing its baleful work. Slothful servants are\nincreasing the evil by their lazy habits.... But the earth has bless-\nings hidden in its depths for those who have courage and will and\nperseverance to gather its treasures.—Fundamentals of Christian\nEducation, 315-327.\nWho will be missionaries to do this work, to teach proper meth-\nods to the youth and to all who feel willing and humble enough to\nlearn?—Fundamentals of Christian Education, 324.\n[232] Work and Study Benefit Both the Earth and the"
