r the benefit of\nhumanity....\nThe cultivation of our land requires the exercise of all the brain-\npower and tact we possess. The lands around us testify to the indo-\nlence of human beings. We hope to arouse to action the dormant\nsenses. We hope to see intelligent farmers who will be rewarded\nfor their earnest labor. The hand and heart must cooperate, bring-\ning new and sensible plans into operation in the cultivation of the\nsoil.—Testimonies to Ministers and Gospel Workers, 242-244.\n[233] Cooperating With God in Work Promotes"
