ercise their mental powers to a\ndegree leads them to view their condition as worse than it really is....\nThose who have broken down by physical exertion must have\nless labor, and that which is light and pleasant. But to shut them\naway from all labor and exercise would in many cases prove their\nruin.... Inactivity is the greatest curse that could come upon such.\nTheir powers become so dormant that it is impossible for them\nto resist disease and languor, as they must do in order to regain\nhealth.—Testimonies for the Church 1:554-556.\n[298] Health Reform and Third Angel’s Message Closely"
